qas.question: How can you identify a duck from other poultry?

answers.text: medium-sized aquatic birds with broad bills, eyes on the side of the head, fairly long necks, short legs set far back on the body, and webbed feet.

qas.question: What do you call a male duck?
How can you identify a drake from a the female of the species?

answers.text: larger than females (simply known as ducks) and are differently coloured in some breeds

qas.question: What does the diet of cultivated ducks consistof ?

answers.text: aquatic insects, molluscs, worms, small amphibians, waterweeds, and grasses.

qas.question: Do all ducks fly south for the winter?

answers.text: Most domestic ducks are too heavy to fly

qas.question: Why can't you identify a duck from other poultry?
What can you never call a male duck?

plausible_answers.text: aquatic insects, molluscs, worms, small amphibians, waterweeds, and grasses
